Durban - A woman believed to be in her 50s was killed in a head-on collision on the N2 North Bound before the M25 Kwa Mashu Highway just after 9am on Friday morning. According to Garrith Jamieson Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find "total chaos." "Two vehicles had collided head on and left both drivers entrapped in the wreckages. Immediately the Durban Fire Department as well as Advanced Life Support Paramedics were dispatched to assist on the scene. "Paramedics found a female believed to be in her fifties had sustained major injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for her and she was declared deceased on the scene. "The second driver had sustained moderate injuries and was stabilised on the scene by Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being freed by the Durban Fire Department. He was then carefully extricated before being transported to a nearby hospital for further care. Traffic was severely affected as only one lane of traffic was open. SAPS  were on scene. POST